TITLE: ELECTION SPOTLIGHT: Jennifer-Ruth Green on Inflation Reduction Act, competing in 'toss-up' midterm race
SUMMARY: Jennifer-Ruth Green, running in Indiana's First Congressional District, talked Inflation Reduction Act, midterm candidate Rep. Frank Mrvan, and why she is the best candidate for the seat.

TITLE: Wisconsin Dem Senate candidate chaired state task force linking racism to climate change
SUMMARY: Senate candidate Mandela Barnes, D-Wis., was appointed to lead a task force that concluded the state must fight climate change by educating government entities on anti-racism.

TITLE: Mitt Romney says Liz Cheney 'would not' win the GOP nomination 'if she were to run' in 2024
SUMMARY: Former Republican presidential nominee Mitt Romney said Rep. Liz Cheney, who has teased a White House run in 2024, would not win the GOP nomination. Romney won the nomination in 2012.

TITLE: Pence says he didn't take classified material, calls for 'unprecedented transparency' after Mar-a-Lago raid
SUMMARY: Former Vice President Mike Pence answered questions regarding the FBI's raid on former President Donald Trump's Florida estate, his handling of classified materials and Liz Cheney.

TITLE: Trump legal counsel vows 'Fourth Amendment based' challenge to Mar-a-Lago raid 'very soon'
SUMMARY: An attorney for former President Trump said in an interview on the Mark Levin Show that they are preparing to file a Fourth Amendment-related legal challenge against the Department of Justice "very soon."

TITLE: Georgia election law provision blasted by Democrats allowed to stand for midterms amid legal challenges
SUMMARY: A Georgia judge determined it was too close to the general election to consider changing the state's rule about handing out food and water within 150 of polling places.

TITLE: Federal court rules DOJ must release internal memo to then-AG Barr stating Trump didn't obstruct justice
SUMMARY: A federal appeals court ruled on Friday that the DOJ must release an internal memo to then-AG Bill Barr which was made to determine if then-President Trump obstructed justice.

TITLE: Sen. Grassley says McConnell is aiming to 'wake people up' with threat that GOP might lose Senate
SUMMARY: Sen. Chuck Grassley is backing up comments from Senate Minority Leader Mitch McConnell that the GOP may lose the Senate, saying the leader is aiming to "wake people up."

TITLE: Iowa state fair attendees say Biden 'too old' to run in 2024, motivated to vote by high inflation
SUMMARY: Iowa voters at the state fair tell Fox News Digital that Biden is too old to run for a second term and that inflation and the economy are their top voting issues heading into the midterms.

TITLE: Louisiana Democrat running for Senate highlights effort from party leaders to stifle election chances
SUMMARY: Gary Chambers, a Democrat running for Senate in Louisiana, says he has faced pushback from state party leadership and that the party should do more "touting" of Biden's accomplishments.

TITLE: Most Californians do not want Biden or Trump to run for president in 2024, poll shows
SUMMARY: A new Berkeley IGS Polls survey revealed most Californians do not want to see either President Biden or former President Trump run in 2024. They prefer new leadership.

TITLE: Texas Gov. Abbott pledges to keep sending illegal immigrants to NYC, DC despite mayorsâ€™ outrage
SUMMARY: Texas Gov. Greg Abbott is promising to keep sending illegal immigrants to New York City and Washington D.C. amid a continuing feud with the sanctuary cities.

TITLE: Catholic group spending $1M on ad slamming Biden for inaction against attacks on pro-life centers, churches
SUMMARY: A Catholic group has launched a $1 million dollar ad campaign to pressure Biden into action against attacks against pro-life pregnancy centers and churches.

TITLE: WH Chief of Staff Ron Klain claims Biden's 'historic achievements' will help Democrats in November midterms
SUMMARY: Biden Chief of Staff Ron Klain is spinning the administration's performance, attempting to build support for Democrats ahead of the November midterm elections.

TITLE: Tim Ryan accused of violating House Ethics rule during Ohio Senate campaign
SUMMARY: Ohio Democratic Rep. Tim Ryan is accused of violating House ethics rules by using images and video of floor proceedings in his bid for the U.S. Senate.

TITLE: Border Patrol nab illegal immigrant with conviction for raping child under age of 4
SUMMARY: Border Patrol agents arrested an illegal immigrant with prior convictions including for possession of a controlled substance and sex with a child three years or younger.

TITLE: Ron Klain says Biden not 'creating a s--tstorm every day' like Trump
SUMMARY: White House Chief of Staff Ron Klain said during an interview that President Biden isn't "creating a s--tstorm every day" like former President Trump did.

TITLE: Democratic Rep. Marcy Kaptur touts 'fighting back' against Biden weeks after embracing him on campaign trail
SUMMARY: Ohio Democratic Rep. Marcy Kaptur changed her tune on President Biden in a new ad that states she "doesn't work for Joe Biden," despite welcoming him with open arms weeks ago.

TITLE: Judge blocks Florida 'woke' law pushed by Gov. DeSantis
SUMMARY: A Florida law restricting critical race theory in both schools and businesses that was supported Gov. Ron Desantis' was blocked by a state judge because it violates the 1st Amendment.

TITLE: Texas Democrat in tight congressional race claims no 'chaos' at southern border, accuses GOP of hyping crisis
SUMMARY: Texas Democrat Michelle Vallejo claimed there was no "chaos" at the U.S. southern border, and accused Republicans of hyping the crisis.
